      • ofEntries

        @SafeVarargs
public final <K,V> java.util.Map<K,V> ofEntries(java.util.Map.Entry<? extends K,? extends V>... entries)
        Constructs a new unique map from a given set of entries. If no entries are provided emptyMap() is returned. The constructed map is not concurrent. Entries can easily be created using entry(Object, Object)
        Type Parameters:
        K - The (super)type of all keys in the entry set
        V - The (super)type of all values in the entry set
        Parameters:
        entries - The entries to use while constructing a new map
        Returns:
        The new non-concurrent map
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - If a entry is null
        See Also:
        entry(Object, Object)
